Day 1
I learned how to open and use the integrated terminal within an editor like VS Code.
I learned to use the pwd command to see my current directory path so I don't get lost.
I learned how to use the history command to look back at my last 20 commands and track my progress.
I learned how to build my workspace as I used the mkdir command to create a specific directory for my Linux work on my Desktop.
I learned to use cd to enter that new directory.
I used the touch command to create my first practice file Day1.
I learned to use ls to see a detailed list of my files, including their sizes and timestamps.